cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with optimal delivery schemes for coded caching problems, which involve information theory and network coding concepts, making cs.IT the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses error-prone links during the delivery phase, which falls under the scope of cs.NI (networking and internet architecture). The use of caching and prefetching techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The proposed optimal error correcting delivery scheme involves system optimization, which could be relevant to cs.SY (systems and control). Finally, the use of coding theory and optimization techniques could also make cs.CC (computational complexity) a possible sub-category.
